T1  - The effect of changes in the federal funds rate target on market interest rates in the 1970s
AU  - Cook, Timothy
AU  - Hahn, Thomas
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 24
IS  - 3
SP  - 331
EP  - 351
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/11/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(89)90025-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393289900251
AB  - This paper examines the influence of monetary policy on interest rates by estimating the effect of changes in the federal funds rate target — the Federal Reserve's policy instrument — on market interest rates in the 1970s. We find that changes in the target caused large movements in short-term rates and smaller but significant movements in intermediate- and long-term rates. We hypothesize that the similarity of the reactions of three-, six-, and twelve-month rates to changes in the target offers a possible explanation for the lack of support for the expectations theory from studies that have tested the theory using these rates.
